### Edit Mode Quick-Add Buttons (Latest - January 2025)

**"+" buttons appear on variable tiles when bottom drawer is open**:
- Creates an "edit mode" experience for the entire project
- When drawer is closed, "+" buttons disappear
- **Self-reference prevention**: Button hidden on the variable currently being edited (prevents recursion)

**Locations**:
- **String cards in canvas**: "+" button in action buttons area (alongside copy/overflow menu)
- **Conditional variables in sidebar**: "+" button in action buttons area (alongside copy/edit/overflow)
- **NOT on spawn variables**: Spawns don't have this button

**Behavior**:
- If editing a **string variable**: Clicking "+" embeds `{{variableName}}` at end of content
- If editing a **conditional variable**: Clicking "+" adds clicked variable as a spawn
- Toast notifications confirm the action ("Added {{hash}} as spawn" or "Added {{hash}} to content")
- Works seamlessly with global search to find and add variables quickly

**Styling**:
- **Filled ShadCN button** (default variant, not outline)
- **Color-coded by action**:
  - Teal (`--string-var-color`) when embedding into a string variable
  - Orange (`--conditional-var-color`) when adding as spawn to a conditional
- White plus icon
- Matches size of adjacent action buttons
- Tooltip shows action ("Add as spawn" or "Embed in content")

